    "body": "Is there a way to just assert the type on an enlargement?\n\nI'm trying to avoid this...\n\n```\nIn [1]: import pandas as pd\n\nIn [2]: names_df = pd.DataFrame(\n   ...:             {\"id\":pd.Series([], dtype='int64')\n   ...:              })\n   ...: names_df.dtypes\n   ...: \nOut[2]: \nid    int64\ndtype: object\n\nIn [3]: names_df.loc[0, \"id\"] = 3\n   ...: names_df.dtypes\n   ...: \nOut[3]: \nid    float64\ndtype: object\n```\n"
  },
